<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="354" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,573,2041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1905,1932]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species differs from other congeneric species by the following characteristics: pronotum fulvous with a central black marking from anterior margin to posterior margin, elytra black with a fulvous apical spot; spermathecal basal half about the same thickness; dorsal central sclerite sub-trapezoidal, with some irregular processes.
</paragraph>
